  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators conducted a controlled trial to assess the effectiveness of electronic
      medical record (EMR) reminders, with or without a panel manager, on completion of health care
      proxy, osteoporosis screening, and influenza and pneumococcal vaccinations for patients age
      65 or older. The investigators hypothesized that EMR reminders would improve adherence to
      practice guidelines and that benefits would be enhanced with the support of a panel manager.
    </textblock>
